{
  "verses": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "The LORD Will Not Forget His People"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "1",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "O LORD, God of vengeance, O God of vengeance, shine forth."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "2",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Rise up, O Judge of the earth; render a reward to the proud."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "3",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "How long will the wicked, O LORD, how long will the wicked exult?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "4",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "They pour out arrogant words; all workers of iniquity boast."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "5",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "They crush Your people, O LORD; they oppress Your heritage."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "6",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "They kill the widow and the foreigner; they murder the fatherless."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "7",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "They say,"
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "The LORD does not see; the God of Jacob pays no heed.",
          "speaker": "Unknown"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "8",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Take notice, O senseless among the people! O fools, when will you be wise?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "9",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He who affixed the ear, can He not hear? He who formed the eye, can He not see?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "10",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He who admonishes the nations, does He not discipline? He who teaches man, does He lack knowledge?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "11",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "The LORD knows the thoughts of man, that they are futile. [^203]"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "12",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Blessed is the man You discipline, O LORD, and teach from Your law,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "13",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "to grant him relief from days of trouble, until a pit is dug for the wicked."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "14",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "For the LORD will not forsake His people; He will never abandon His heritage."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "15",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Surely judgment will again be righteous, and all the upright in heart will follow it."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "16",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Who will rise up for me against the wicked? Who will st and for me against the workers of iniquity?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "17",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Unless the LORD had been my helper, I would soon have dwelt in the abode of silence."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "18",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "If I say,"
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "My foot is slipping,",
          "speaker": "Unknown"
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Your loving devotion, O LORD, supports me."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "19",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "When anxiety overwhelms me, Your consolation delights my soul."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "20",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Can a corrupt throne be Your ally—one devising mischief by decree?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "21",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "They band together against the righteous and condemn the innocent to death. [^204]"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "22",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "But the LORD has been my stronghold, and my God is my rock of refuge."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "23",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He will bring upon them their own iniquity and destroy them for their wickedness.\nThe LORD our God will destroy them."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    }
  ]
}